{
  "texts": [
    "All methods incorporated a hyperparameter called Maximum Deletion Ratio (𝑀𝐷𝑅), where 𝑀𝐷𝑅 defined the maximum random deletion rate of input text during training, and the average deletion rate was set to 𝑀𝐷𝑅/2.",
    "Pre-trained uncased BERT-base was used for fine-tuning.",
    "The model consisted of 12 Transformer blocks, with a hidden layer size of 768 and 12 self-attention modules, totaling 1.1 million parameters.",
    "During fine-tuning, a dropout probability of 0.1 was maintained, and the number of training epochs was set to 10.",
    "The initial learning rate was set to 2𝑒 -5, with a batch size of 24."
  ]
}